00:03:33.260 --> 00:03:34.523
both the implicit,

00:03:36.180 --> 00:03:37.255
both the explicit,

00:03:37.255 --> 00:03:39.160
the ones that you're actually
paying money for explicitly

00:03:39.160 --> 00:03:40.920
and the implicit opportunity costs.

00:03:40.920 --> 00:03:42.810
Total opportunity costs,

00:03:42.810 --> 00:03:44.340
that's total opportunity cost

00:03:44.340 --> 00:03:46.310
and the difference between
your total revenue,

00:03:46.310 --> 00:03:49.990
so for a given quantity,
the difference between

00:03:49.990 --> 00:03:53.751
your total revenue and your
total opportunity cost,

00:03:53.751 --> 00:03:56.060
that gives you your economic profit.

00:03:56.060 --> 00:03:57.500
For this quantity right over here,

00:03:57.500 --> 00:03:59.500
your economic profit would be represented

00:03:59.500 --> 00:04:04.500
by the height of this little
bar between these two curves.

00:04:04.580 --> 00:04:06.560
But what we see what's going on is,

00:04:06.560 --> 00:04:08.040
as we increase the quantity over here,

00:04:08.040 --> 00:04:10.370
these curves are getting
further and further apart.

00:04:10.370 --> 00:04:12.945
That's because the green
curve, the total revenue,

00:04:12.945 --> 00:04:17.230
it's slope is larger
